{"id":"1710.07518","submitter":"Ruben Hidalgo","authors":"Grzegorz Gromadzki and Ruben A. Hidalgo","title":"Structural description of dihedral extended Schottky groups and\n  application in study of symmetries of handlebodies","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Given a symmetry $\\tau$ of a closed Riemann surface $S$, there exists an\nextended Kleinian group $K$, whose orientation-preserving half is a Schottky\ngroup $\\Gamma$ uniformizing $S$, such that $K/\\Gamma$ induces $\\langle \\tau\n\\rangle$; the group $K$ is called an extended Schottky group. A geometrical\nstructural description, in terms of the Klein-Maskit combination theorems, of\nboth Schottky and extended Schottky groups is well known. A dihedral extended\nSchottky group is a group generated by the elements of two different extended\nSchottky groups, both with the same orientation-preserving half. Such\nconfiguration of groups corresponds to closed Riemann surfaces together with\ntwo different symmetries and the aim of this paper is to provide a geometrical\nstructure of them. This result can be used in study of three dimensional\nmanifolds and as an illustration we give the sharp upper bounds for the total\nnumber of connected components of the locus of fixed points of two and three\ndifferent symmetries of a handlebody with a Schottky structure.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Oct 2017 13:04:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 25 Feb 2022 12:51:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-28"}
